---
import PrivacyDoc from '@/layouts/PrivacyDoc.astro';
import { apps } from '@/data/apps';

const app = apps.find((a) => a.id === 'qr-and-barcode')!;
---

<PrivacyDoc app={app}>
  <p>
    QR and Barcode respects your privacy. This app is designed to work primarily on your device and
    does not require you to create an account.
  </p>

  <h2>Information We Collect</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Camera access for scanning QR codes and barcodes</li>
    <li>Scan content you choose to scan</li>
    <li>History data saved locally on your device</li>
    <li>App settings such as theme and preferences</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>How We Use Information</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Scanning QR codes and barcodes</li>
    <li>Showing scan results</li>
    <li>Saving scan history on your device</li>
    <li>Remembering your app preferences</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Data Storage</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Scan history is stored locally on your device</li>
    <li>App preferences are stored locally on your device</li>
    <li>No account registration is required</li>
    <li>The app does not intentionally upload scan history to our servers</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Permissions</h2>
  <p>The app requests camera permission so you can scan QR codes and barcodes.</p>

  <h2>Sharing</h2>
  <p>
    If you choose to use share features, the content you share is sent only through the system
    sharing options you select.
  </p>

  <h2>Third-Party Services</h2>
  <p>
    The current version of the app does not require sign-in or cloud sync. If analytics, crash
    reporting, or other third-party services are added in a future release, this Privacy Policy
    should be updated before release.
  </p>

  <h2>Android 13 and Advertising ID</h2>
  <p>
    The current version of QR and Barcode does not use the Android advertising ID for ads or
    profiling and does not require advertising features to use the core scanning experience.
  </p>

  <h2>Data Retention</h2>
  <p>Your scan history remains on your device until you delete it or uninstall the app.</p>

  <h2>Children's Privacy</h2>
  <p>
    This app is not directed specifically to children, and we do not knowingly collect personal
    information from children through a backend service.
  </p>

  <h2>Security</h2>
  <p>No method of storage or transmission is completely secure.</p>

  <h2>Your Choices</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Deny camera permission</li>
    <li>Delete saved history from the app</li>
    <li>Uninstall the app to remove locally stored app data, subject to device behavior</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>Contact email: <code>enesk6u@gmail.com</code></p>

  <h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
  <p>
    We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. When we do, we will update the date at the
    top of this document.
  </p>
</PrivacyDoc>
